Also this year, a Hubertus Mass is celebrated on the feast day of St. Hubert in St. Mary's Church on the sleeve mountain road.
St. Hubertus was according to legend a fairly ruthless hunter who was converted by a vision and later appointed bishop of Liege.
The hunting horn the hunt group riders Westphalia under the direction of Brigitte Kluth performs on par force horns (natural horns in the mood Es) according to the old, original French melodies.
The brass wear riding clothes because they accompany mainly riders, horses and hounds in tow hunts musical.
The solemn mass will be held on Sunday 3rd November, at 11.30 clock.
